   Subsurface Science Initiative
   Opportunities
   Related Links: Existing Collaborations.
     __________________________________________________________________



        The INEEL Subsurface Science Initiative is actively recruiting in
                                             the following discipline areas...
                                                                   Biosciences
                                                                   Geosciences
                                                                     Chemistry
                                                                      Modeling

             We are recruiting for Technical Leads in chemistry, modeling, and
            biological sciences. Leads are responsible for developing research
          programs for their respective disciplines, within the context of the
         overarching goals and vision of the Subsurface Science Initative. Our
          online job postings are currently being reorganized. Postings can be
           found at http://jobs.inel.gov. If you do not see a posting for your
             area of expertise, please contact Mike Wright, Subsurface Science
                   Initiative Director, at (208) 526-3315, or wrigpm@inel.gov.

      Research, Postdocs & Fellowships - Learn about opportunities for joint
      research, postdoctoral research and fellowship programs in subsurface
      science at INEEL
      Collaborations - Collaborative interdiscplinary research is crucial to
      achieving the goals of the INEEL Subsurface Science Initiative. Learn
   more about institutional and researcher-to-researcher collaborations.

   Page contact: Deborah Hill, subsurf@inel.gov.

